blueprint.description:
128MW sustained (i.e. both day & night)
Or x 10/100/1000 if upgraded using "Advanced Solar" mod.

The ratio here is NOT 0.84.  It's 0.964 or about 15% higher than strictly necessary.  This allows setting a monitor and global alert: If accumulators drop below 15%, you're consuming more power than you're producing and A BLACKOUT IS IMMINENT!

Better to have some extra accumulator power and get a warning/buffer than immediate blackout.  Lose the outside ring of accumulators if you don't want this.
blueprint.label: Solar (128MW)
